## 1.2.0 (2026-06-23)

* Raised the minimum PHP version from 7.4 to 8.0.
* Added a public `encrypt()` method that produces a payload `decrypt()` can read back (fresh random IV and salt per call).
* Added an `InvalidArgumentException` when `decrypt()` is called with a payload too short to contain an IV and salt.
* Extracted the cipher, hash, and segment-length magic numbers into named class constants with an explanatory comment.
* Extracted key derivation into a shared private `deriveKey()` helper used by both `encrypt()` and `decrypt()`.
* Refactored the test suite to exercise the public `encrypt()` method instead of inlining the encryption protocol.
* Documented the encryption scheme (cipher, key derivation, payload table) and added a security note to the README.

## 1.1.0 (2026-01-28)

* Added `declare(strict_types=1)` for runtime type enforcement.
* Added PHP 7.4 typed properties to `Decrypter` class.
* Added `RuntimeException` when calling `decrypt()` before setting encrypted content.
* Added `RuntimeException` when `openssl_decrypt` fails (e.g. wrong key or corrupt payload).
* Added explicit `void` return types on `setDecryptKey()` and `setEncryptedContent()`.
* Fixed constructor parameter from nullable default (`string $decryptKey = null`) to required (`string $decryptKey`).
* Fixed empty-key check from truthy (`!$decryptKey`) to explicit (`$decryptKey === ''`).
* Fixed PHPDoc `@var` and `@param` types from non-existent types to correct scalar types.
* Fixed class opening brace placement to follow PSR-12.
* Replaced placeholder class docblock with protocol documentation.
* Added PHPUnit 9.6 test suite with 10 unit tests covering constructor validation, decryption with a known test vector, error handling, setters, and round-trip encrypt/decrypt.

## 1.0.0 (2025-02-01)

* The initial release of the PHP decrypter.